summary: ok sorry but it’s not just the pride symbolism of Dorothy/Judy/the rainbow/etc (which would be... ugh..amazing), and the idea of...
body: ok sorry but it’s not just the pride symbolism of Dorothy/Judy/the rainbow/etc (which would be… ugh..amazing), and the idea of going from black and white to screaming colour but then STILL learning there’s no place like home, and the duality of the good and the bad witch!!! there’s also the idea of the wizard as the (wo)man behind the curtain, the unseen orchestrator of all PR/politics, the ‘you never get just what you see’ concept, that is a very important theme in The Wizard of Oz and basically I’m SHAKING

tags: i might be kinda dumb like i said before
summary:
I have no idea if anyone has already addressed this but... 
I was just having a good ole country bop when I realised the Dixie...
body:
The ‘home’ ts7 theory

I have no idea if anyone has already addressed this but…

I was just having a good ole country bop when I realised the Dixie chicks have an album titled home. What art work features on the wall of the apartment in the ME! video among the ‘cool chicks’…

That would be none other than the Dixie chicks!

Is this more than coincidence? I’m leaning towards no myself but who knows.

I might just be kinda dumb and haven’t fully read into this theory, completely missing when other clever people figured this out before me, but i figured this was some pretty convincing supporting evidence for the whole home theory 🤷‍♀️

I see you miss swift💕 @taylorswift
